<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">Marshall S.
                                    Carter</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-05">5 January 1947</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>89012. Reur 1907. The President stated his complete agreement to your
                            views expressed in reference message. The White House press release will
                            be made at 1900 Monday 6 January Eastern Standard Time for use of radio
                            that night and for morning papers Tuesday 7 January.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>